\section{Development Environment and Technologies}

\textit{Inside My System} was developed as a browser-based interactive
application using JavaScript and Three.js. The development process was
carried out on Linux, using a modular project structure and a local
development server provided by Vite.

Three.js was selected as the main graphics library because it provides
a higher-level interface to WebGL while preserving direct control over
the fundamental elements of a real-time three-dimensional application,
including scenes, cameras, lights, materials, textures, meshes and the
rendering loop. This made it possible to focus on the design of the
interactive experience without having to manually implement the
lower-level WebGL initialisation and buffer-management procedures.

Vite was used as the development and build tool. During development, it
provided a fast local server and automatic module reloading. For the
final release, it generated the optimised production bundle deployed
through GitHub Pages.

The three-dimensional assets were created and prepared in Blender.
Models were exported in the binary glTF format (\texttt{.glb}), which
can preserve mesh geometry, materials, object hierarchies and texture
references in a format suitable for web applications. The imported
models were then positioned, configured and animated programmatically
inside the Three.js scene.

